Umar Muhammed, Lafia The Senator representing Nasarawa West in the National Assembly, Abdullahi Adamu, has said Governor Abdullahi Sule remains the choice of members of the All Progressives Congress come 2023. Adamu, who is the first civilian governor of the state, said this when he led a delegation of stakeholders from the zone on a solidarity visit to the Sule in the Government House, Lafia, on Sunday. He said, “No member of the party from the zone will contest against you come 2023. This is our resolve. We are in the government house to commend you for your exemplary leadership, as well as restate our loyalty to your administration. “We are here to tell the world that we have nobody from our zone who will contest against you, you are our candidate come 2023.” Adamu explained that the people of the state, especially those from his senatorial zone, were appreciative of the governor’s developmental strides since he assumed office a little after one year ago. The delegation specifically praised the governor for ongoing road construction, the Karu Mega Bus Terminal, the Keffi Square and Neighbourhood Market, which they all noted were geared towards improving the economic well-being of the people of the zone. They also commended him for his initiative in the area of security, noting that actions so far taken by his administration had restored peace across the state. Earlier, Sule expressed gratitude to the delegation for their show of solidarity and promised to continue to run an all-inclusive government as well as ensure the even distribution of developmental projects across the state. Copyright PUNCH.
